        <h3>
         First Kaplan Pioneer Graduate Fellowship announced
        </h3>
        <p>
         The Center for biological physics is pleased to announce the first Kaplan Pioneer Graduate Fellowship will be awarded to Mr. Krishna Choudhary. This award, made possible by the generous donations of Mr. Richard Kaplan, is intended to support research in an area that promises to open new fields of study in biological physics. The first winner is Mr. Krishna Choudhary for his work on neuronal mechanics associated with locating the individual in space and time.
         <a href="http://cbp.physics.ucla.edu/first-kaplan-pioneer-award">
